34
00:01:55,734 --> 00:01:57,601
Look, i get it.

35
00:01:57,634 --> 00:01:59,968
You have other things on your mind.

36
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,133
I don't expect

37
00:02:01,167 --> 00:02:03,567
to be the person at the
top of your priority list.

38
00:02:15,868 --> 00:02:18,501
Clark kent.

39
00:02:18,534 --> 00:02:21,667
He can save an entire city
in the blink of an eye,

40
00:02:21,701 --> 00:02:23,634
but when it comes to ladies,

41
00:02:23,667 --> 00:02:26,801
the red-blue blur still
drives with the brakes on.

42
00:02:26,834 --> 00:02:28,801
Linda lake.

43
00:02:28,834 --> 00:02:30,667
What are you doing here?

44
00:02:30,701 --> 00:02:32,100
Watching you.

45
00:02:32,133 --> 00:02:34,133
Impressive as always.

46
00:02:34,167 --> 00:02:37,133
You're a murderer. You
should be in prison.

47
00:02:37,167 --> 00:02:39,200
The police cleared my name.

48
00:02:39,234 --> 00:02:41,734
Besides, there's no prison sentence

49
00:02:41,767 --> 00:02:43,934
worse than where i've been ...

50
00:02:43,968 --> 00:02:46,167
circling the drain of obscurity.

51
00:02:48,501 --> 00:02:49,901
I'm a nobody, kent.

52
00:02:49,934 --> 00:02:53,767
Two years living underground
dried up my prophetic pen.

53
00:02:53,801 --> 00:02:58,267
But i'm ready to make another splash.

54
00:02:58,300 --> 00:03:00,701
Haven't your stories
ruined enough lives?

55
00:03:00,734 --> 00:03:02,701
Oh, no.

56
00:03:02,734 --> 00:03:04,367
It's different this time.

57
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:08,701
I want to be the voice
of the red-blue blur.

58
00:03:08,734 --> 00:03:12,501
Every rescue, every takedown,

59
00:03:12,534 --> 00:03:16,767
every kitten that you
rescue from a tree,

60
00:03:16,801 --> 00:03:20,234
you leak the story to me first.

61
00:03:20,267 --> 00:03:22,701
My name will be known alongside yours

62
00:03:22,734 --> 00:03:24,634
