00:16:07,301 --> 00:16:10,433
I-it was basically a long,
rambling, awkward apology.

265
00:16:10,467 --> 00:16:12,301
Look, i-i wasn't blowing you off.

266
00:16:12,334 --> 00:16:14,301
It's just that with jimmy's recovery

267
00:16:14,334 --> 00:16:16,268
and then losing a chunk of my memory

268
00:16:16,301 --> 00:16:19,001
after the wedding from
hell, i was ... yeah, okay.

269
00:16:19,034 --> 00:16:21,201
See, this is exactly
why i went out of town.

270
00:16:21,234 --> 00:16:22,834
I need to give you some space.

271
00:16:22,867 --> 00:16:24,334
No space is necessary.

272
00:16:24,368 --> 00:16:27,901
Davis, look, let's just
forget that this ever happened.

273
00:16:27,934 --> 00:16:30,201
The problem is i can't seem to do that.

274
00:16:31,634 --> 00:16:34,967
You have been nothing
but a good friend to me.

275
00:16:36,967 --> 00:16:39,700
I just ...  i don't think
that will ever be enough.

276
00:16:41,767 --> 00:16:44,234
So i take it friendship's off the table?

277
00:16:44,268 --> 00:16:47,867
Chloe, a friendship like ours...

278
00:16:49,934 --> 00:16:52,433
it can be dangerous.

279
00:16:55,834 --> 00:16:58,134
I guess this is goodbye then.

280
00:17:05,334 --> 00:17:07,634
<i>You actually know her?</i>

281
00:17:07,667 --> 00:17:09,268
Yeah, so?

282
00:17:09,301 --> 00:17:11,400
So? She's famous!

283
00:17:11,433 --> 00:17:14,433
She's the kryptonian's best friend!

284
00:17:22,700 --> 00:17:25,034
Kryptonian.

285
00:17:29,567 --> 00:17:32,234
Ready to earn your
stripes as city editor?

286
00:17:32,268 --> 00:17:33,334
Linda lake.

287
00:17:33,368 --> 00:17:35,834
Well, there's a name i
haven't seen in a while.

288
00:17:35,867 --> 00:17:39,201
Here to reclaim the stiletto
out of your assistant's back?

289
00:17:40,234 --> 00:17:41,500
We both know

290
00:17:41,533 --> 00:17:44,467
this news rag's nothing more
than poor man's wallpaper.

291
00:17:44,500 --> 00:17:46,567
Just here to make it readable again.

292
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:48,368
Clear your page one. Run this.

293
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:51,034
We stopped throwing your
gossip grenades years ago.

294
00:17:51,067 --> 00:17:53,767
Don't forget that while
you were chasing ambulances

295
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:54,867
with the other cubs,

296
00:17:54,901 --> 00:17:56,867
i was breaking real news.

297
00:17:56,901 --> 00:17:59,433
My blog had more hits
than the chicago mob.

298
00:17:59,467 --> 00:18:02,268
My name was feared and
revered around the world.

299
00:18:02,301 --> 00:18:03,600
<i>I'm doing you a favor.</i>

300
00:18:03,634 --> 00:18:07,334
Do yourself a favor,
lake. Get a new career.

301
00:18:07,368 --> 00:18:09,533
It's about the alien.

302
00:18:15,934 --> 00:18:17,567
We're live from the smallville farmhouse

303
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:19,867
where up until this morning
clark kent lived in anonymity.

304
00:18:19,901 --> 00:18:21,167
Now the crowds are gathering

305
00:18:21,201 --> 00:18:23,001
to try and get a peek at
the superhero next door.

306
00:18:23,034 --> 00:18:24,001
There she is.

307
00:18:24,034 --> 00:18:25,301
Chloe sullivan,

308
00:18:25,334 --> 00:18:27,600
what's it like having an
alien as a best friend?

309
00:18:27,634 --> 00:18:30,767
I'm, uh, just trying to get inside.

310
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:33,034
Mom, what do you mean, "forced leave"?

311
00:18:33,067 --> 00:18:35,134
Can they even do that to a senator?

312
00:18:35,167 --> 00:18:37,268
Okay, look. This will all blow over.

313
00:18:37,301 --> 00:18:39,234
People just need time to adjust.

314
00:18:39,268 --> 00:18:41,301
All right. I'll talk to you later.

315
00:18:42,767 --> 00:18:44,767
Clark, it's chloe!

316
00:18:49,167 --> 00:18:51,167
The beatles have landed in smallville.

317
00:18:51,201 --> 00:18:52,201
You okay?

318
00:18:54,934 --> 00:18:56,334
<i>Yeah, i'm fine.</i>

319
00:18:56,368 --> 00:18:58,433
<i>How are you dealing with
the instant star status?</i>

320
00:18:58,467 --> 00:19:00,834
Unfortunately, my 15 minutes
of fame have no end in sight.

321
00:19:00,867 --> 00:19:03,368
Well, i don't mean
to add to the fanfare,

322
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:06,167
but lois was just given
an editor's promotion.

323
00:19:06,201 --> 00:19:07,600
And congratulations ...

324
00:19:07,634 --> 00:19:10,967
you now have a penthouse office
right next to tess mercer.

325
00:19:11,001 --> 00:19:15,301
<i>Man on tv: clark kent's
not everyone's hero.</i>

326
00:19:18,234 --> 00:19:22,634
<i>Last week, a crane collapsed
at my husband's work site</i>

327
00:19:22,667 --> 00:19:24,800
<i>and killed him.</i>

328
00:19:24,834 --> 00:19:27,301
<i>Where was clark kent then?</i>

329
00:19:27,334 --> 00:19:30,800
<i>Who says he gets to choose</i>

330
00:19:30,834 --> 00:19:32,901
<i>who lives and who dies?</i>

331
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:40,567
Clark, right now we need to
focus on finding linda lake.

332
00:19:40,600 --> 00:19:42,934
Now, i think i know why she went m.i.a.

333
00:19:42,967 --> 00:19:45,800
It turns out that linda
shared a cellblock with me

334
00:19:45,834 --> 00:19:46,834
in black creek.

335
00:19:46,867 --> 00:19:48,533
She can turn herself into water, chloe.

336
00:19:48,567 --> 00:19:49,800
Why didn't she just escape?

337
00:19:49,834 --> 00:19:51,467
Because electricity is her kryptonite.

338
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:53,634
Linda lake's specialized restraints

339
00:19:53,667 --> 00:19:56,967
discharged a chemical
electrical bonding current,

340
00:19:57,001 --> 00:19:59,934
meaning it basically kept her solid.

341
00:19:59,967 --> 00:20:02,600
<i>Great, then all we have to do is find
her. Man on tv: we now take you live</i>

342
00:20:02,634 --> 00:20:04,067
<i>to a press conference with linda lake.</i>

343
00:20:04,101 --> 00:20:06,234
<i>Shouldn't be too hard.
Lake: clark kent...</i>

344
00:20:06,268 --> 00:20:08,767
<i>is not a hero.</i>

345
00:20:08,800 --> 00:20:11,934
<i>He's not a savior.</i>

346
00:20:11,967 --> 00:20:14,400
<i>He's not even a friend.</i>

347
00:20:14,433 --> 00:20:21,567
<i>He is the first wave of
an all-out alien invasion.</i>

348
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:26,134
<i>My detailed investigation has revealed</i>

349
00:20:26,167 --> 00:20:31,567
that clark kent is to
blame for meteor showers,

350
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:33,700
deadly power outages,

351
00:20:33,734 --> 00:20:37,901
and an unspeakable
trail of human carnage.

352
00:20:37,934 --> 00:20:42,667
When it rains, it pours.

353
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:46,134
<i>A hero that tried to stop this alien</i>

354
00:20:46,167 --> 00:20:49,667
<i>before it ravaged our homeland again.</i>

355
00:20:49,700 --> 00:20:52,500
<i>And that hero...</i>

356
00:20:52,533 --> 00:20:55,034
<i>that hero was lex luthor.</i>

357
00:20:56,667 --> 00:21:00,400
<i>And clark kent killed him.</i>

358
00:21:02,467 --> 00:21:03,201
She just turned me into a public enemy.

359
00:21:03,234 --> 00:21:05,500
E just turned me into a public enemy.

360
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:09,500
<i>Clark, you need to leave. Now.</i>

361
00:21:09,533 --> 00:21:11,101
I can straighten this out, chloe.

362
00:21:11,134 --> 00:21:12,834
I'll talk to the authorities myself.

363
00:21:12,867 --> 00:21:14,834
It looks like they want
to talk to you, too.

364
00:21:14,867 --> 00:21:16,767
Look, clark, this is
only gonna get worse.

365
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:18,533
You need to leave while you still can.

366
00:21:18,567 --> 00:21:20,800
I'm not running, chloe.
People need to know the truth.

367
00:21:20,834 --> 00:21:22,600
Now, why don't you
go out the back, okay?

368
00:21:22,634 --> 00:21:24,368
I'll catch up with you later.

369
00:21:27,067 --> 00:21:28,734
Be careful.

370
00:21:49,033 --> 00:21:50,768
Linda lake is lying through her teeth.

371
00:21:50,801 --> 00:21:52,067
Her points line up, clark.

372
00:21:52,100 --> 00:21:54,434
So why don't you just tell
me who you're working with?

373
00:21:54,467 --> 00:21:56,334
Like i said, i'm not
working with anyone.

374
00:21:56,367 --> 00:21:57,334
I was sent here alone.

375
00:21:57,367 --> 00:21:58,868
To do what ... work on a farm?

376
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:01,100
It's pretty clear there's
a bigger agenda here.

377
00:22:01,134 --> 00:22:03,033
Look, my father sent me
here with a dying wish

378
00:22:03,067 --> 00:22:04,868
that i use my abilities
to protect mankind.

379
00:22:04,900 --> 00:22:06,134
It's what i've always done.

380
00:22:06,167 --> 00:22:07,667
It's what i'm gonna continue to do.

381
00:22:07,701 --> 00:22:10,134
And i'm sure if i ask your
friends, they'll attest to that?

382
00:22:10,167 --> 00:22:12,467
Hmm? Friends like lois lane?

383
00:22:12,501 --> 00:22:16,200
You gave her the front
page of a lifetime.

384
00:22:16,234 --> 00:22:18,267
Now, if she's been keeping your secret,

385
00:22:18,300 --> 00:22:21,033
she could be aiding and
abetting an enemy of the state.

386
00:22:21,067 --> 00:22:22,367
No, lois is innocent.

387
00:22:22,401 --> 00:22:24,667
Everything she knows is in her story.

388
00:22:24,701 --> 00:22:26,033
And chloe sullivan?

389
00:22:26,067 --> 00:22:28,501
Impressive how long
she kept your secret.

390
00:22:28,534 --> 00:22:31,134
How many other secrets
is she keeping, clark?

391
00:22:31,167 --> 00:22:34,667
Look, i have been open about
everything you've asked me.

392
00:22:34,701 --> 00:22:37,033
And i appreciate it. I really do.

393
00:22:37,067 --> 00:22:39,501
I'm sure you won't have any problem

394
00:22:39,534 --> 00:22:41,501
with us running some tests.

395
00:22:41,534 --> 00:22:43,634
No one agreed to any tests ...

396
00:22:43,667 --> 00:22:46,667
only to answer the
questions... you asked of me.

397
00:22:46,701 --> 00:22:51,000
Just calm down, and everything
will be fine, all right?

398
00:22:51,033 --> 00:22:52,434
No one's running any tests.

399
00:22:56,134 --> 00:22:57,701
Fire!

400
00:23:15,067 --> 00:23:17,768
Keep your car running.
The feds are after you.

401
00:23:17,801 --> 00:23:20,000
What did they do to you?
It doesn't matter, chloe.

402
00:23:20,033 --> 00:23:21,501
You have to leave smallville now.

403
00:23:21,534 --> 00:23:23,167
<i>Man on radio: we
interrupt this broadcast</i>

404
00:23:23,200 --> 00:23:24,601
<i>to bring you a special bulletin.</i>

405
00:23:24,634 --> 00:23:27,067
<i>Authorities are on a statewide
manhunt for clark kent.</i>

406
00:23:27,100 --> 00:23:28,234
<i>He's considered dangerous,</i>

407
00:23:28,267 --> 00:23:29,933
<i>unpredictable, and without remorse.</i>

408
00:23:29,967 --> 00:23:32,434
<i>Granville county has issued a
mandatory curfew of 9:00 p.m.</i>

409
00:23:32,467 --> 00:23:33,967
<i>And urges families with children</i>

410
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:35,801
<i>to stay indoors at all times.</i>

411
00:23:40,100 --> 00:23:42,567
Do they know about the
meteor rocks? Not yet.

412
00:23:42,601 --> 00:23:45,701
That's why they're after you ...
to find a way to stop me, chloe.

413
00:23:45,734 --> 00:23:47,801
We have to leave town separately. What?

414
00:23:47,834 --> 00:23:49,634
Am i losing you, clark?

415
00:23:49,667 --> 00:23:51,967
If this is goodbye, i'm not saying it.

416
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:54,033
No, chloe, when this all
dies down, i'll find you.

417
00:23:54,067 --> 00:23:55,033
I promise.

418
00:23:55,067 --> 00:23:56,534
This isn't gonna die down, clark.

419
00:23:56,567 --> 00:23:58,900
There has to be a way that
we could just undo everything.

420
00:23:58,933 --> 00:24:00,401
I mean, can't you just ask jor-el

421
00:24:00,434 --> 00:24:02,067
to orchestrate another second chance?

422
00:24:02,100 --> 00:24:03,200
He's gone, chloe.

423
00:24:03,234 --> 00:24:04,933
He disappeared when
the fortress went dark.

424
00:24:04,967 --> 00:24:07,134
Then unless you're hiding
some sort of latent power

425
00:24:07,167 --> 00:24:08,933
to turn back time, i have no more ideas.

426
00:24:10,434 --> 00:24:11,734
The legion.

427
00:24:11,768 --> 00:24:14,300
They gave me a ring that
makes time travel possible.

428
00:24:14,334 --> 00:24:16,100
I hid it in a toolbox in the barn.

429
00:24:16,134 --> 00:24:18,234
I never thought i'd
have to use it, but...

430
00:24:18,267 --> 00:24:20,967
you think you can go back
to before your story broke?

431
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:23,300
The legion went back
1,000 years using it.

432
00:24:23,334 --> 00:24:25,467
Okay, now, i know i
don't need to remind you

433
00:24:25,501 --> 00:24:27,900
what happened last time
you turned back the clock.

434
00:24:27,933 --> 00:24:30,067
There's always a consequence.

435
00:24:31,467 --> 00:24:32,933
The world fears me, chloe,

436
00:24:32,967 --> 00:24:35,967
and as long as they know who i am...

437
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:39,000
i can't help them.

438
00:24:39,033 --> 00:24:41,334
I don't have a choice.

439
00:24:52,567 --> 00:24:53,801
Clark, call me.

440
00:24:53,834 --> 00:24:56,067
Whatever trash these people
are spreading about you,

441
00:24:56,100 --> 00:24:59,000
you can count on me to
fire back, guns blazing.

442
00:25:00,567 --> 00:25:02,367
You sit across from the guy, lane.

443
00:25:02,401 --> 00:25:04,734
How slow are you?

444
00:25:10,267 --> 00:25:12,100
Oh, hell no.

445
00:25:15,834 --> 00:25:18,300
Hold that elevator!

446
00:25:23,200 --> 00:25:24,367
Last i checked,

447
00:25:24,401 --> 00:25:27,200
stories required these
little things called "facts."

448
00:25:27,234 --> 00:25:30,367
Maybe the city editor is
willing to print your fiction,

449
00:25:30,401 --> 00:25:33,000
but tess mercer will
gladly run my rebuttal.

450
00:25:33,033 --> 00:25:36,300
I'm sorry, katie, i'm ... i'm
gonna have to call you back.

451
00:25:36,334 --> 00:25:39,367
My connection just took on
a terrible whining sound.

452
00:25:39,401 --> 00:25:40,701
Okay, thanks.

453
00:25:42,334 --> 00:25:44,167
Katie couric.

454
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:47,634
You see a parade, and you just
have to rain on it, don't you?

455
00:25:47,667 --> 00:25:49,067
You can't stand the fact

456
00:25:49,100 --> 00:25:52,000
that there are actually
good people in this world.

457
00:25:55,401 --> 00:25:58,534
If your boyfriend really
cared about saving people...

458
00:25:59,868 --> 00:26:01,768
...he would've done things my way.

459
00:26:01,801 --> 00:26:03,467
People looked up to him.

460
00:26:03,501 --> 00:26:06,601
He could've been the
hero they always needed.

461
00:26:06,634 --> 00:26:08,701
Funny thing about people ...

462
00:26:08,734 --> 00:26:12,300
the only thing they love
more than building up heroes

463
00:26:12,334 --> 00:26:13,834
is tearing them down.

464
00:26:18,801 --> 00:26:20,734
Tess, what were you thinking?

465
00:26:20,768 --> 00:26:22,000
Man: she's up here.

466
00:26:24,067 --> 00:26:25,933
Miss lane, we need to speak with you

467
00:26:25,967 --> 00:26:27,967
regarding matters of national security.

468
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:29,067
Without my lawyer,

469
00:26:29,100 --> 00:26:31,334
you're not gonna hear
me so much as hiccup.

470
00:26:40,300 --> 00:26:42,300
Nice interception, but
you shouldn't be here.

471
00:26:42,334 --> 00:26:45,367
All the bloodhounds in the state
will be sniffing you out. It's okay.

472
00:26:45,401 --> 00:26:46,567
I know this sounds crazy,

473
00:26:46,601 --> 00:26:48,367
but in a few moments,
this will all be over.

474
00:26:48,401 --> 00:26:49,467
Okay, well, try me.

475
00:26:49,501 --> 00:26:51,401
My shock threshold is
pretty high right now.

476
00:26:51,434 --> 00:26:52,501
Lois, i have a ring

477
00:26:52,534 --> 00:26:55,834
that allows me to go
to any moment in time.

478
00:26:55,868 --> 00:26:57,167
I'm gonna go back

479
00:26:57,200 --> 00:27:00,334
to before linda lake
ever wrote that article.

480
00:27:00,367 --> 00:27:03,300
The world isn't ready to
accept someone like me.

481
00:27:04,367 --> 00:27:06,100
Then stay and fight back.

482
00:27:06,134 --> 00:27:09,801
Look, give people a chance
to see who you really are.

483
00:27:09,834 --> 00:27:10,933
It's too late, lois.

484
00:27:10,967 --> 00:27:13,067
My whole life, i've seemed different.

485
00:27:14,634 --> 00:27:17,933
Some people spend their entire lives

486
00:27:17,967 --> 00:27:20,933
looking for a way to stand out...

487
00:27:20,967 --> 00:27:25,167
to be a person that
anybody would call special.

488
00:27:25,200 --> 00:27:28,367
When you first told me who you were...

489
00:27:28,401 --> 00:27:32,834
my thought was, "anyone but clark."

490
00:27:32,868 --> 00:27:34,834
And not because of the alien thing.

491
00:27:34,868 --> 00:27:36,267
I... i've known enough guys

492
00:27:36,300 --> 00:27:38,367
to know that you can
be born on terra firma

493
00:27:38,401 --> 00:27:40,834
and be light-years from normal.

494
00:27:40,868 --> 00:27:43,967
Lois, you don't have
to explain. I get it.

495
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:46,334
No, you don't.

496
00:27:49,667 --> 00:27:53,334
How can someone with
x-ray vision be so blind?

497
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:59,200
I've been down the hero road before.

498
00:28:00,868 --> 00:28:03,868
And every time, i made a giant u-turn.

499
00:28:06,534 --> 00:28:08,667
But this...

500
00:28:08,701 --> 00:28:11,667
this was different.

501
00:28:13,234 --> 00:28:15,567
<i>And this time, it will
be different, lois.</i>

502
00:28:15,601 --> 00:28:18,300
When i do this, no one's
gonna remember who i am.

503
00:28:20,033 --> 00:28:23,367
And when you hit your reset button...

504
00:28:25,701 --> 00:28:29,234
...you're not gonna tell
me your secret, are you?

505
00:28:32,134 --> 00:28:33,933
I'm sorry.

506
00:28:35,933 --> 00:28:37,933
That's okay.

507
00:28:39,933 --> 00:28:42,933
Why should i think i'm special?

508
00:28:45,267 --> 00:28:47,734
Clark...

509
00:28:49,734 --> 00:28:51,567
i understand.

510
00:28:53,801 --> 00:28:56,134
Lois, you don't understand.

511
00:28:58,134 --> 00:29:00,900
<i>It's because you are special.</i>

512
00:29:08,067 --> 00:29:10,834
I have to go.

513
00:29:31,200 --> 00:29:34,134
Looking for this?

514
00:29:57,300 --> 00:29:58,834
Oh, my god. What happened?

515
00:29:58,868 --> 00:30:01,968
Chloe, i am so sorry. It's all a lie.

516
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:03,734
I thought that i could stop it.

517
00:30:03,767 --> 00:30:06,067
Davis, look at me.
Tell me what's going on.

518
00:30:06,100 --> 00:30:07,901
I'm gonna go get you some
help. No! No, you can't!

519
00:30:07,934 --> 00:30:10,000
Nothing helps.

520
00:30:10,033 --> 00:30:11,167
What are these?

521
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:12,801
I built up a tolerance.

522
00:30:12,834 --> 00:30:14,000
I can't control it anymore.

523
00:30:14,033 --> 00:30:15,467
<i>Control what?</i>

524
00:30:15,501 --> 00:30:18,033
The beast.

525
00:30:19,400 --> 00:30:21,667
You must have blacked it out.

526
00:30:21,701 --> 00:30:23,567
You were in the arctic with me.

527
00:30:23,601 --> 00:30:26,801
You told me it was my destiny
to kill the other kryptonian.

528
00:30:26,834 --> 00:30:28,501
What are you saying, davis?

529
00:30:28,534 --> 00:30:31,501
<i>"The other kryptonian" ...
there's only one kryptonian.</i>

530
00:30:31,534 --> 00:30:32,667
There's only clark.

531
00:30:32,701 --> 00:30:36,334
I'm...kryptonian.

532
00:30:41,400 --> 00:30:42,868
You're doomsday.

533
00:30:42,901 --> 00:30:46,968
I was sent to this planet to kill clark.

534
00:30:48,701 --> 00:30:50,601
You stay away from him.

535
00:30:50,634 --> 00:30:52,000
You have to warn him, chloe.

536
00:30:52,033 --> 00:30:53,767
Something's been drawing me back here.

537
00:30:53,801 --> 00:30:55,367
I thought that it was you, but no.

538
00:30:55,400 --> 00:30:57,067
It was clark.

539
00:31:02,100 --> 00:31:03,734
Davis, your eyes...

540
00:31:03,767 --> 00:31:06,767
chloe, run.

541
00:31:06,801 --> 00:31:08,234
Get out of here!

542
00:31:12,734 --> 00:31:14,801
Lois, i need you to
give a message to clark.

543
00:31:14,834 --> 00:31:16,334
He's not picking up his phone.

544
00:31:16,367 --> 00:31:18,767
That creature that was at
my wedding is davis bloome,

545
00:31:18,801 --> 00:31:20,601
and he's coming for clark!

546
00:31:43,968 --> 00:31:46,734
I used to think a lot about rings.

547
00:31:46,767 --> 00:31:49,834
I thought getting one meant
i'd found true happiness.

548
00:31:49,868 --> 00:31:53,267
But there is no such thing as
true happiness in this world,

549
00:31:53,300 --> 00:31:54,400
is there?

550
00:31:54,434 --> 00:31:57,234
Not when you only see the bad in people.

551
00:31:59,634 --> 00:32:01,934
Look how fast they turned on you.

552
00:32:01,968 --> 00:32:04,634
One second, you're on top of the world.

553
00:32:04,667 --> 00:32:05,968
And the next,

554
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:09,534
it's as if your life story's
written in someone else's blood.

555
00:32:09,567 --> 00:32:10,834
Not that i care.

556
00:32:10,868 --> 00:32:13,300
This trumps your blur any day.

557
00:32:13,334 --> 00:32:14,767
That ring ... it's dangerous.

558
00:32:14,801 --> 00:32:15,801
No.

559
00:32:15,834 --> 00:32:18,968
This ring is every journalist's dream.

560
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:21,801
I'll know stories before they break.

561
00:32:21,834 --> 00:32:25,701
<i>The entire world will know me.</i>

562
00:32:48,601 --> 00:32:49,968
The rock.

563
00:32:51,334 --> 00:32:53,334
Are you okay? I'll be all right.

564
00:33:01,367 --> 00:33:03,467
Chloe just called.

565
00:33:03,501 --> 00:33:07,000
You're not gonna believe
this, but davis...

566
00:33:24,300 --> 00:33:27,767
i know what you're planning.

567
00:33:27,801 --> 00:33:29,767
Mr. Kent.

568
00:33:29,801 --> 00:33:31,701
I was just thinking about you.

569
00:33:31,734 --> 00:33:34,334
Two years is too long
to go without a visit.

570
00:33:34,367 --> 00:33:36,501
You're not gonna run my story.

571
00:33:39,434 --> 00:33:40,734
Your story?

572
00:33:40,767 --> 00:33:44,067
Oh, so now you're not
just super, you're psychic.

573
00:33:44,100 --> 00:33:45,667
I'm a journalist now.

574
00:33:45,701 --> 00:33:48,000
I brought you my latest work.

575
00:33:50,467 --> 00:33:52,267
It's about all the
murders you committed.

576
00:33:54,667 --> 00:33:57,067
People are gonna know
who you really are,

577
00:33:57,100 --> 00:33:59,100
and your word will mean nothing.

578
00:34:00,734 --> 00:34:02,767
You're going to jail.

579
00:34:04,234 --> 00:34:06,234
I don't think so.

580
00:34:28,834 --> 00:34:31,434
No one can ever know my name.

581
00:34:45,567 --> 00:34:47,134
Some things never change.

582
00:34:47,167 --> 00:34:48,601
I've been gone a month,

583
00:34:48,634 --> 00:34:51,334
and you still drive in the granny lane.

584
00:34:53,334 --> 00:34:55,401
You're welcome for the ride, lois.

585
00:34:55,434 --> 00:34:57,800
Did i mention i missed
your ongoing commentary?

586
00:34:57,833 --> 00:34:58,967
No, actually,

587
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:01,534
and aside from asking me
what the speed limit was,

588
00:35:01,567 --> 00:35:03,967
you barely said a
word on the way home...

589
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:05,800
or since i've been
gone, for that matter,

590
00:35:05,833 --> 00:35:07,900
unless you count the
three 10-second voicemails.

591
00:35:07,933 --> 00:35:09,867
Lois, you know, after the wedding,

592
00:35:09,900 --> 00:35:11,467
things got a little crazy.

593
00:35:12,734 --> 00:35:15,567
Things got a little crazy
before all hell broke loose.

594
00:35:15,601 --> 00:35:17,200
Let's face it.

595
00:35:18,768 --> 00:35:20,734
<i>Or ... or we could not face it</i>

596
00:35:20,768 --> 00:35:24,100
and just forget that
it ever almost happened.

597
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:29,334
I think it's a pretty
complicated conversation, lois.

598
00:35:31,267 --> 00:35:33,534
We don't have to
overanalyze anything now.

599
00:35:36,267 --> 00:35:39,100
I'm gonna work off my jet lag
later on tonight at the cafe.

600
00:35:39,134 --> 00:35:41,000
You want to come by for a coffee, cool.

601
00:35:41,034 --> 00:35:42,800
If not, let's just say i get it.

602
00:35:42,833 --> 00:35:45,467
Okay.

603
00:35:45,501 --> 00:35:47,501
Okay. See you then.

604
00:35:49,434 --> 00:35:51,200
Or not. Or whatever.

605
00:35:51,234 --> 00:35:53,734
I'm going to work.

606
00:36:00,401 --> 00:36:01,434
I have to admit,

607
00:36:01,467 --> 00:36:03,900
i would've loved to have seen clark kent

608
00:36:03,933 --> 00:36:06,134
as an international-celebrity icon.

609
00:36:06,167 --> 00:36:07,434
It wasn't a pretty sight.

610
00:36:07,467 --> 00:36:09,301
Yeah, but being a
part of your entourage,

611
00:36:09,334 --> 00:36:10,867
<i>i must've had some perks, right?</i>

612
00:36:10,900 --> 00:36:14,100
If you consider complete
invasion of privacy a perk.

613
00:36:14,134 --> 00:36:16,301
Though there was this one moment

614
00:36:16,334 --> 00:36:19,067
right after i told
lois the truth about me.

615
00:36:19,100 --> 00:36:21,501
I thought everything would be okay.

616
00:36:21,534 --> 00:36:24,100
Thought i could have
it all, but i was wrong.

617
00:36:26,200 --> 00:36:27,467
You know, clark,

618
00:36:27,501 --> 00:36:30,000
<i>maybe you can have your
cape and wear it, too.</i>

619
00:36:30,034 --> 00:36:32,833
Say that clark kent, the
unassuming journalist,

620
00:36:32,867 --> 00:36:35,334
buttoned up in a starched shirt and tie,

621
00:36:35,367 --> 00:36:37,668
but then, when he's playing the hero,

622
00:36:37,701 --> 00:36:39,768
he ... steps out of the
shadow into his red and blue,

623
00:36:39,800 --> 00:36:41,501
creating two completely
separate identities?

624
00:36:41,534 --> 00:36:42,501
Yeah.

625
00:36:42,534 --> 00:36:45,601
And for the cherry on top,

626
00:36:45,634 --> 00:36:48,601
you get to tell lois the truth
and still know her reaction.

627
00:36:48,634 --> 00:36:51,701
All of this made one
thing very clear, chloe ...

628
00:36:51,734 --> 00:36:54,267
lois can never know who i really am.

629
00:36:54,301 --> 00:36:57,034
Clark, is it safe to say
that maybe another benefit

630
00:36:57,067 --> 00:36:58,534
from protecting your secret

631
00:36:58,567 --> 00:37:01,234
is getting to protect
yourself from getting hurt?

632
00:37:03,833 --> 00:37:05,833
I destroyed the legion ring.

633
00:37:08,833 --> 00:37:10,800
Speaking of that...

634
00:37:10,833 --> 00:37:14,668
controlling time ...
it's too dangerous, chloe.

635
00:37:14,701 --> 00:37:17,200
It always comes at a price.

636
00:37:17,234 --> 00:37:22,833
Trust me, i'm thrilled that
you got a page-one rewrite.

637
00:37:22,867 --> 00:37:25,567
But it kind of makes me wonder

638
00:37:25,601 --> 00:37:28,134
what might've changed this time.

639
00:37:41,200 --> 00:37:43,167
Can i ask you what you're doing?

640
00:37:43,200 --> 00:37:48,401
Davis bloome ... i'm
one of the, uh, emts.

641
00:37:48,434 --> 00:37:53,467
Oh, well, there's actually a
patient who's looking for you.

642
00:38:05,634 --> 00:38:07,134
Uh, there must be some mistake.

643
00:38:07,167 --> 00:38:08,501
I don't know you.

644
00:38:08,534 --> 00:38:12,634
While i've been puddling around
metropolis for the last week,

645
00:38:12,668 --> 00:38:15,367
i've seen lots of interesting stories.

646
00:38:15,401 --> 00:38:19,534
What a nice surprise to stumble
upon your dirty little secret.

647
00:38:19,567 --> 00:38:23,967
Painful breathing, pale complexion...

648
00:38:24,000 --> 00:38:27,933
unsightly bone protrusions.

649
00:38:36,900 --> 00:38:39,034
You don't know what
you're talking about.

650
00:38:39,067 --> 00:38:40,034
Right.

651
00:38:40,067 --> 00:38:43,067
You just have a terrible skin condition.

652
00:38:44,234 --> 00:38:46,634
What do you want from me?

653
00:38:46,668 --> 00:38:50,933
I want you to release the beast

654
00:38:50,967 --> 00:38:54,267
and break me out of these restraints.

655
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:59,000
It doesn't exactly work like that.

656
00:39:00,867 --> 00:39:03,234
Don't waste your time with the pills.

657
00:39:03,267 --> 00:39:05,067
I've seen what you can do.

658
00:39:05,100 --> 00:39:06,200
You don't understand.

659
00:39:06,234 --> 00:39:08,067
You don't know what you're dealing with!

660
00:39:08,100 --> 00:39:10,000
<i>No. You don't understand.</i>

661
00:39:10,034 --> 00:39:13,067
I can't spend another
second trapped in a cell.

662
00:39:13,100 --> 00:39:16,467
Do you want me to tell
chloe who you really are?

663
00:39:22,067 --> 00:39:24,034
That's a good boy.

664
00:39:24,067 --> 00:39:26,167
Become the thing you're meant to be.

665
00:39:26,200 --> 00:39:27,501
Stop.

666
00:39:27,534 --> 00:39:28,833
Let it go.

667
00:39:28,867 --> 00:39:30,134
Shut up!

668
00:39:30,167 --> 00:39:31,434
Set me free!

669
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:04,668
Oh, my god.

670
00:41:54,100 --> 00:41:57,067
For Seriessub.com

